# Codebase Indexing

**Indexing Configuration:**
- Enable codebase indexing for large projects
- Configure index refresh frequency
- Set up incremental indexing
- Optimize index size

**Indexing Best Practices:**
- Index source code directories
- Exclude node_modules, .next, build
- Include documentation in index
- Update index on significant changes

**Index Configuration:**
See `.cursor/index-config.json` for detailed configuration.

**Include Patterns:**
- `app/**` - Next.js app directory
- `components/**` - React components
- `lib/**` - Utility libraries
- `docs/**` - Documentation

**Exclude Patterns:**
- `node_modules/**` - Dependencies
- `.next/**` - Build output
- `build/**` - Build artifacts
- `dist/**` - Distribution files

**Refresh Strategy:**
- `on-change` - Update index when files change
- Incremental updates for performance
- Full refresh on major changes

**Large Codebase Optimization:**
- Use incremental indexing
- Focus on frequently accessed files
- Optimize index size
- Use targeted searches with @Codebase

